A '''cricket''' is a type of [[cockpit]] audio alert onboard [[commercial aircraft]] such as those of [[Airbus]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.airbus.com/fileadmin/media_gallery/files/safety_library_items/AirbusSafetyLib_-FLT_OPS-TOFF_DEP-SEQ08.pdf|publisher=Airbus|date=4 May 2005|title=Flight Operations Briefing Notes|accessdate=12 December 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.smartcockpit.com/data/pdfs/plane/airbus/A320/misc/A320_Flight_Deck_and_Systems_Briefing_For_Pilots.pdf|title=A319/A320/A321 Flightdeck and Systems Briefing for Pilots|date=8 October 2006}}</ref>  Its sound is intentionally designed to be extremely difficult for pilots to ignore.  The "chirp chirp" sound is named after the [[Cricket (insect)|insect]] that it imitates.

