'''Mineral cosmetics''' are forms of [[make-up]] that are composed of compressed [[mineral]]s.<ref name=health>{{cite book |title=Beauty Pure and Simple: The Ayurvedic Approach to Beautiful Skin |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QV-PqiHcnVcC&pg=PA102&dq=mineral+cosmetics&hl=en&sa=X&ei=3VFiT9SlFMP20gH-07yNCA&ved=0CEkQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=mineral%20cosmetics&f=false |page=102 |accessdate=March 15, 2012 |publisher=Shambhala Publications |author=Kristin Ma |year=2001}}</ref> Most of these products are pure mineral, and do not contain any [[Oil additive|oil or wax additives]].<ref>{{cite book |title=The Truth About Beauty: Transform Your Looks And Your Life From The Inside Out |author=Kat James, Oz Garcia |year=2003 |publisher=Simon and Schuster |page=EBook, page not given |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=P1F8PsOYqGkC&pg=PT172&dq=mineral+cosmetics+iron&hl=en&sa=X&ei=p1RiT_eHKcrv0gGZ7Ny7CA&ved=0CFMQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=mineral%20cosmetics%20iron&f=false}}</ref> Some kinds of minerals can have beneficial health results for the skin, combining health effects with cosmetic results.<ref name=health /> The claim that applying minerals directly to the skin in the form of cosmetics has health benefits, however, has inspired some scientific controversy.<ref>{{cite news |publisher=Women's Health |page=111 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EMYDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA111&dq=mineral+cosmetics&hl=en&sa=X&ei=3VFiT9SlFMP20gH-07yNCA&ved=0CFQQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=mineral%20cosmetics&f=false |accessdate=March 15, 2012 |author=Maria Ricapito |date=November 2006 |title=Is it Really Healthily, Prettier, Better--The Dirt on the Mineral Make-up Craze}}</ref> Historically some mineral additives have proven to be poisonous to the skin, such as [[Lead poisoning|lead]].<ref>{{cite book |title=Lead and Lead Poisoning in Antiquity |year=1983 |publisher=Wiley |author=Jerome O. Nriagu |pages=23, 131, 299}}</ref> However the kinds of minerals used in modern products are not harmful to the skin.<ref name=health />

